examples.en: The lake has more than 20 varieties of fish.
The nature became a selector of varieties.
The minuter diversifications are called varieties.
The two lads represent two distinct varieties of human life.
Men differ greatly in their appreciation of varieties of vowel sound.
Just when autumn had begun to tinge the woods with a thousand beautiful varieties of colour.
Unlike France, Italy relies on dozens of indigenous regional grape varieties for its prodigious range of wines.
Harvesting wild mushrooms is no business for amateurs, since some of the esculent ones closely resemble poisonous varieties.
